Consider the following suggestion:

```
[[registry]]
prefix="docker.io"
blocked = false

endpoints = [
{
   location = "docker.io"
},
{
   location = "mirror.local"
   insecure = true
   pull-through = true
},
{
   location = "registry.rewrite.me"
   insecure = true
}
]
```

The prefix stays as is and is *mandatory*. The top-level registry can also be blocked, nothing more. Unqualified registries are specified as suggested above.

The `endpoints` table contains *all* possible registry and does not distinguish between the "main" one or a "mirror". If no endpoint is specified we could add the `prefix` as a default one for lazy users such as I am.
